  {
    "type": "EXEGETICAL (ORIGINAL LANGUAGES)",
    "name": "Cambridge Bible for Schools and Colleges",
    "elements": [
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "bld",
        "text": "55",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ". ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "saw the glory of God",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "] Some visible sign of God’s presence such as the Shechinah had been to the Jews of old. See ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Exodus 16:10",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "; ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Exodus 24:17",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", in the latter of which passages it is described as like devouring fire. It is defined by the Jews as the concentration of God’s omnipresence.",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "p",
        "text": "",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "br",
            "class": "",
            "text": "",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "br",
            "class": "",
            "text": "",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "and Jesus standing on the right hand of God",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "] i.e. he was permitted to behold Jesus triumphing in the flesh in which He had been crucified. The position of ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "standing",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " rather than that of ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "sitting",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " as described elsewhere (",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Matthew 26:64",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", &c.) may have been to indicate the readiness of Jesus to strengthen and help His martyr.",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "p",
        "text": "",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "br",
            "class": "",
            "text": "",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "br",
            "class": "",
            "text": "",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      }
    ]
  },
  {
    "type": "EXEGETICAL (ORIGINAL LANGUAGES)",
    "name": "Bengel's Gnomen",
    "elements": [
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Acts 7:55",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ". ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "greekheb",
        "text": "Πλήρης",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "full",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ") As the fury of his enemies increases, the strength of spirit in Stephen increases, as also every fruit of the Spirit.—",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "greekheb",
        "text": "ἀτενίσας",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "having looked stedfastly",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ") By an earnest look to ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "heaven",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", the mind of those dying by a violent death may be raised up.—",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "greekheb",
        "text": "εἶδε",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "he saw",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ") Jesus is not said to have addressed Stephen.—",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "greekheb",
        "text": "δόξαν Θεοῦ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "the glory of God",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ") the ineffable splendour which shines forth in the third heaven.—",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "greekheb",
        "text": "ἐστῶτα",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "standing",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ") as if to meet Stephen. Comp. ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Acts 7:59",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ". For everywhere else he is said ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "to sit",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ". Arator well writes,—",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "p",
        "text": "",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "br",
            "class": "",
            "text": "",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "br",
            "class": "",
            "text": "",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "“Lumina cordis habens cœlos conspexit apertos",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "p",
        "text": "",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "br",
            "class": "",
            "text": "",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "br",
            "class": "",
            "text": "",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "Ne lateat, quid Christus aget: pro martyre surgit.",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "p",
        "text": "",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "br",
            "class": "",
            "text": "",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "br",
            "class": "",
            "text": "",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "Quem tunc ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "stare",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " videt, confessio nostra ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "sedentem",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "p",
        "text": "",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "br",
            "class": "",
            "text": "",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "br",
            "class": "",
            "text": "",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "Cum soleat celebrare magis. Caro juncta Tonanti",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "p",
        "text": "",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "br",
            "class": "",
            "text": "",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "br",
            "class": "",
            "text": "",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "In Stephano favet ipsa sibi: Dux præscius armat",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "p",
        "text": "",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "br",
            "class": "",
            "text": "",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "br",
            "class": "",
            "text": "",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "Quos ad dona vocat.”",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "p",
        "text": "",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "br",
            "class": "",
            "text": "",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "br",
            "class": "",
            "text": "",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "“By the light that shone into his heart he beheld the heavens opened, so that it does not escape his glance what Christ is doing there: He rises for the martyr, whom the latter at that time sees ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "standing",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "; whereas our confession (creed) is wont rather to celebrate Him as ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "sitting",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ". The flesh itself, assumed by the Thunderer, favours, in the case of Stephen, its own self. The prescient Captain of our salvation arms those, whom He calls to gifts.”",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "p",
        "text": "",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "br",
            "class": "",
            "text": "",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "br",
            "class": "",
            "text": "",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "",
        "children": []
      }
    ]
  },
  {
    "type": "EXEGETICAL (ORIGINAL LANGUAGES)",
    "name": "Pulpit Commentary",
    "elements": [
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "cmt_sub_title",
        "text": "Verse 55.",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " - ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "cmt_word",
        "text": "Looked up steadfastly",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " (",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "greek",
        "text": "ἀτενίσας",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "); see ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Acts 6:15",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "; ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Acts 3:4",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", and note. The glory of God; ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "accented",
        "text": "i.e.",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " the visible glory which surrounds and proclaims God's near presence (see ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Exodus 24:10, 16, 17",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "; ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Isaiah 6:1-3",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "; ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Ezekiel 1:28",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "; ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Revelation 21:14, 23",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", etc.). ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "cmt_word",
        "text": "Jesus standing.",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " Sitting at the right hand of God is the usual attitude ascribed to our Lord in token of his victorious rest, and waiting for the day of judgment. Here he is seen standing, as rising to welcome his faithful martyr, and to place on his head the crown of life ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Revelation 2:10",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "). Whether Stephen saw these glorious things in the flesh or out of the flesh he probably knew not himself. Acts 7:55",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "",
        "children": []
      }
    ]
  },
